      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable that you're looking for the most cost-effective way to manage your symptoms, but self-medication, especially with corticosteroids like albuterol, can be dangerous without a doctor's guidance. Your symptoms could indicate that your asthma needs to be adjusted, but increasing your medications on your own might lead to harmful side effects or a worsening situation. It’s essential to discuss your symptoms with your healthcare provider to get professional advice. They might suggest visiting sooner rather than later for an updated evaluation and to adjust your treatment plan accordingly.",
